==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trilemma
<hw>Tri*lem"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/
(see <er>Tri-</er>) + <er><?/</er> any thing received, in logic, an
assumption. Cf. <er>Dilemma</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld>
<def>A syllogism with three conditional propositions, the major premises
of which are disjunctively affirmed in the minor. See
<er>Dilemma</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A state of things in which it is difficult to
determine which one of three courses to pursue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trilinear</ent>⟦br⟧
